# Backend Architecture (Nikonikkos)

Unified API + filter-based queries + RBAC. **One list endpoint per resource; filters via query params only.**

## 1. Strict API design

Do **not** add fragmented routes such as `/api/products/category/:id`, `/featured`, `/search`, or `/brand/:id`.

Use a single list endpoint:

```
GET /api/products
```

All filtering via query params.

## 2. Filter query params

Support: `category`, `subCategory`, `brand`, `minPrice`, `maxPrice`, `search`, `tags`, `isFeatured`, `isActive`, `sort`, `page`, `limit`, `stockStatus`.

Example:

```
GET /api/products?category=paints&minPrice=1000&maxPrice=5000&sort=price_asc&page=1&limit=20
```

**Search** matches `title`, `description`, `tags`, `brand` (MongoDB text index or regex fallback).

## 3. Controllers (thin)

List handlers delegate to services; **no raw MongoDB query logic in controllers**.

Use a shared query builder from `req.query` (e.g. `buildQuery(req.query)` or service `buildFilter()`).

## 4. Services (business logic)

All DB and filter logic lives in services (e.g. `services/product.service.js`):

- `buildFilter()` / `buildProductFilter(query)`
- `buildSort()`
- `buildPagination()`
- `executeQuery()`

Do not put DB logic in controllers or mix filters in routes.

## 5. RBAC

Roles: `ADMIN`, `MANAGER`, `STAFF`, `CUSTOMER`.

| Role | Access |
|------|--------|
| ADMIN | Full access |
| MANAGER | Products CRUD, orders |
| STAFF | Update orders, inventory only |
| CUSTOMER | Read products, place orders |

Protect routes with existing auth + role middleware:

```js
router.post(
  "/",
  isAuthenticatedUser,
  authorizeRole("ADMIN", "MANAGER"),
  createProduct
);
```

Extend `USER_ROLES` in `config/constants.js` when adding roles; do not bypass RBAC.

## 6. Product model

Required fields: `category` (ObjectId), `subCategory` (ObjectId, optional), `brand` (string), `attributes` (flexible JSON), `pricing` object, `stock` object, `tags[]`, `isFeatured`, `isActive`. No hardcoded filter-only fields.

## 7. Response format

List endpoints return unified shape (extend `utils/response.js` if needed):

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "optional",
  "data": {},
  "meta": { "page": 1, "limit": 20, "total": 200, "pages": 10 }
}
```

## 8. Pagination

`page` (default `1`), `limit` (default `20`) on all list endpoints.

## 9. Sorting

`sort=price_asc|price_desc|newest|oldest` → `{ price: 1 }`, `{ price: -1 }`, `{ createdAt: -1 }`, `{ createdAt: 1 }`.

## 10. Indexes

Product: text on `title`; indexes on `category`, `brand`, `price`, `isFeatured`.

## 11. Filter builder (mandatory)

Centralize in `utils/` (e.g. `buildProductFilter(query)`): category, price range, search, tags, brand, stock. **No duplicate filter logic** across controllers/services.

## 12. File layout

Match repo: `backend/src/controllers/`, `services/`, `models/`, `routes/`, `middlewares/`, `utils/`.

Pattern: Controller → thin; Service → logic; Model → schema; Routes → mapping only.

## 13. Cart & orders

- One cart per user (no guest cart unless explicitly added).
- Orders snapshot product data at purchase time.

## Stop and refactor if

- New list endpoint instead of query filters
- DB logic in controllers
- RBAC bypassed
- Duplicate product services/controllers or filter code
